1
00:00:00,600 --> 00:00:07,067
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:09,833 --> 00:00:11,200
Mike Trinidad is dead.

3
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:14,400
I want to know
where our money is!

4
00:00:14,933 --> 00:00:16,800
That's our suspect.
Samuel Trinidad.

5
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:18,133
Mike's son.

6
00:00:18,267 --> 00:00:19,867
He's currently in the hands
of the police.

7
00:00:19,967 --> 00:00:20,933
He's being interrogated
right now.

8
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:22,233
He can't end up behind bars.

9
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:24,400
He needs to tell us
where the money is!

10
00:00:24,567 --> 00:00:25,933
Rigor mortis
had already set in

11
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:27,567
when the forensic team
examined the body.

12
00:00:27,733 --> 00:00:30,133
This puts the time of death
between 9PM and 10PM.

13
00:00:30,267 --> 00:00:32,867
And based on the
CCTV time stamp,

14
00:00:32,967 --> 00:00:35,467
Samuel Trinidad arrived
at around 11:30PM.

15
00:00:35,633 --> 00:00:37,133
There's powder burn
on the victim's hand.

16
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:38,767
Most probably, it was suicide.

17
00:00:39,467 --> 00:00:40,600
I remember seeing you two.

18
00:00:40,767 --> 00:00:42,267
You both went to your office.

19
00:00:42,433 --> 00:00:45,433
What did you two talk about?
It seemed important.

20
00:00:45,533 --> 00:00:48,500
I'd rather keep to myself
whatever it was we talked about.

21
00:00:52,467 --> 00:00:54,400
Did you personally
know my husband?

22
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:55,600
He is my father.

23
00:00:56,800 --> 00:00:57,800
Dude, what's happening?

24
00:00:57,967 --> 00:01:00,100
The office is gone!
And so is our money, dude!

25
00:01:00,200 --> 00:01:01,467
It's probably buried
with Mike Trinidad!

26
00:01:01,633 --> 00:01:02,500
We've been scammed!

27
00:01:03,667 --> 00:01:05,767
He was too scared
to face his sins.

28
00:01:05,933 --> 00:01:09,767
Mike Trinidad will pay for
his crimes, even in the grave.

29
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:11,633
You're scamming people!

30
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:14,767
There he is! He's down here!

31
00:01:16,667 --> 00:01:17,633
Give us back our money!

32
00:01:19,833 --> 00:01:22,267
Sir, it wasn't just
investment funds Mike took.

33
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:24,200
Even our big accounts
were wiped out.

34
00:01:24,333 --> 00:01:26,767
I have an idea
where he hid all the money.

35
00:01:26,867 --> 00:01:28,500
Just give me some time, sir.

36
00:01:28,667 --> 00:01:30,000
I'll recover all of it.

37
00:01:30,167 --> 00:01:32,267
Leave the son to me.

38
00:01:34,867 --> 00:01:41,700
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

39
00:01:58,833 --> 00:01:59,800
[THEME MUSIC CONCLUDES]

40
00:01:59,900 --> 00:02:00,967
[MAEL] Did I hear you right?

41
00:02:01,067 --> 00:02:02,500
You received an email.

42
00:02:02,900 --> 00:02:04,800
Turns out, the sender is...

43
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:06,633
dead?

44
00:02:07,667 --> 00:02:08,500
Correct?

45
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:09,567
That's right, bro.

46
00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:11,533
How could that happen?

47
00:02:11,700 --> 00:02:12,900
Oh, I know this one.

48
00:02:13,033 --> 00:02:14,500
It's called a scheduled email.

49
00:02:14,700 --> 00:02:16,900
For example,
you write an email today.

50
00:02:17,067 --> 00:02:22,767
You can set it so the recipient
 will receive it next week.

51
00:02:23,567 --> 00:02:24,367
Let's say, hypothetically,

52
00:02:24,467 --> 00:02:26,833
you go out and get hit by a bus

53
00:02:26,933 --> 00:02:28,533
right after sending it.

54
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:31,000
The email will still be
delivered to the recipient

55
00:02:31,100 --> 00:02:32,067
on the scheduled date.

56
00:02:32,733 --> 00:02:34,200
The wonders of modern
technology, right?

57
00:02:34,367 --> 00:02:39,000
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

58
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:40,200
[SIGHS]

59
00:02:43,567 --> 00:02:45,700
[MAN 1] Where is it?!
We need our money!

60
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:46,767
Sir-- [PANTS]

61
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:48,767
Mr. Sanchez is here.

62
00:02:48,933 --> 00:02:50,267
He suddenly showed up.

63
00:02:53,933 --> 00:02:59,300
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

64
00:02:59,433 --> 00:03:02,067
[PEOPLE CLAMORING
IN THE DISTANCE]

65
00:03:02,233 --> 00:03:03,067
Mr. Sanchez--

66
00:03:03,233 --> 00:03:04,400
Is it true?!

67
00:03:04,833 --> 00:03:05,900
Samuel.

68
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,267
The money I invested
in your father...

69
00:03:08,433 --> 00:03:09,767
Is it really gone?

70
00:03:09,933 --> 00:03:12,733
Sir, I had nothing to do
with what my father did.

71
00:03:12,833 --> 00:03:13,800
I wasn't involved.

72
00:03:13,933 --> 00:03:15,100
At all, sir.

73
00:03:15,767 --> 00:03:16,733
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

74
00:03:17,100 --> 00:03:19,600
I invested in him
because of you!

75
00:03:19,767 --> 00:03:20,900
Mr. Sanchez, come on.

76
00:03:21,033 --> 00:03:22,100
- Let's talk--
- No!

77
00:03:22,200 --> 00:03:23,133
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

78
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:25,333
Sir, I know he's my father.

79
00:03:25,467 --> 00:03:27,933
But I had no knowledge
of his investment scheme.

80
00:03:28,033 --> 00:03:29,067
When he came here,

81
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:31,100
that was the first time
I had seen him again

82
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,900
since I was a kid.

83
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:34,133
Believe me.

84
00:03:34,300 --> 00:03:36,000
I had nothing to do with it.

85
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:38,267
I worked hard for that money!

86
00:03:38,367 --> 00:03:39,933
All I can do now is this.

87
00:03:40,033 --> 00:03:41,600
Whatever losses you've suffered,

88
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:43,267
we'll recover them.

89
00:03:43,367 --> 00:03:44,900
I'll take good care
of your portfolio.

90
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:45,900
- No.
- I promise.

91
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,133
Sir, leave it to me.

92
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,100
Pull out my money here!

93
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:50,267
- No, no. Sir--
- Samuel.

94
00:03:50,433 --> 00:03:51,833
- Mr. Sanchez.
- No more trust!

95
00:03:51,967 --> 00:03:53,067
- Don't do this.
- No!

96
00:03:53,167 --> 00:03:54,600
- Mr. Sanchez.
- No!

97
00:03:54,733 --> 00:03:55,667
Sir!

98
00:03:55,833 --> 00:03:58,867
[OVERLAPPING CLAMOR]

99
00:03:59,000 --> 00:03:59,967
[GRUNTS]

100
00:04:01,067 --> 00:04:02,333
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

101
00:04:03,067 --> 00:04:04,200
- [HUFFS]
- [DOOR CLOSES]

102
00:04:06,067 --> 00:04:07,300
[MUSIC FADES OUT]

103
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,300
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

104
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,300
Son.

105
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,933
I saw all the posts
on social media.

106
00:04:17,800 --> 00:04:18,933
Are you okay?

107
00:04:19,033 --> 00:04:20,200
How are you holding up?

108
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:22,667
Ma...

109
00:04:23,667 --> 00:04:25,500
This has already affected
my work.

110
00:04:26,667 --> 00:04:29,700
Because of it,
I lost a major client.

111
00:04:30,700 --> 00:04:32,167
And now, the people
my father scammed

112
00:04:32,267 --> 00:04:33,833
are coming to confront me
at the branch.

113
00:04:34,867 --> 00:04:36,733
[INHALES, EXHALES DEEPLY]

114
00:04:36,867 --> 00:04:37,900
Hang on, Samuel.

115
00:04:38,867 --> 00:04:40,967
Are all the accusations
against your father true?

116
00:04:41,867 --> 00:04:42,733
Seems like it, Ma.

117
00:04:43,100 --> 00:04:44,133
Seems like it.

118
00:04:44,233 --> 00:04:45,467
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

119
00:04:45,567 --> 00:04:48,067
My goodness, your father...

120
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:49,667
He couldn't just help it.

121
00:04:49,833 --> 00:04:52,033
He had to leave behind
a huge mess.

122
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:53,533
I just don't understand him.

123
00:04:54,067 --> 00:04:55,733
Good grief.

124
00:04:57,867 --> 00:05:01,567
[MUSIC BECOMES PENSIVE]

125
00:05:01,733 --> 00:05:02,700
Ma.

126
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:07,367
Ma, what was my first word?

127
00:05:08,900 --> 00:05:10,000
- What?
- My first word.

128
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:12,000
When I was a baby.

129
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:13,667
What did I say first?

130
00:05:15,100 --> 00:05:16,700
Your first word?

131
00:05:16,867 --> 00:05:18,067
First word...

132
00:05:18,233 --> 00:05:19,200
Uh...

133
00:05:19,367 --> 00:05:20,600
"Hello."

134
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:22,267
You said hello.

135
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:24,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

136
00:05:24,467 --> 00:05:27,400
[SAMUEL]
 "Your first word is IVORY."

137
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:35,533
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING]

138
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:45,900
[MUSIC ENDS]

139
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:52,867
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

140
00:05:54,933 --> 00:05:56,033
[ELEVATOR BELL CHIMES]

141
00:05:56,133 --> 00:05:57,300
[ELEVATOR DOORS SLIDE OPEN]

142
00:06:07,967 --> 00:06:14,767
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

143
00:06:14,933 --> 00:06:15,767
[ELEVATOR DOORS CLOSE]

144
00:06:16,933 --> 00:06:19,267
My men have been keeping
a close eye on Samuel.

145
00:06:19,433 --> 00:06:22,467
So far, he hasn't made
any suspicious moves

146
00:06:22,633 --> 00:06:26,433
or shown signs of big purchases.

147
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:29,433
I've also been monitoring
his bank account.

148
00:06:29,533 --> 00:06:31,167
No suspicious activity
there either.

149
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:32,433
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

150
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:35,733
The amount of money is just
too large to hide easily.

151
00:06:37,867 --> 00:06:40,333
But Mike Trinidad?
He was good at it.

152
00:06:43,833 --> 00:06:45,967
Let's hope his son
didn't take after him.

153
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,367
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

154
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:51,800
He will bring us to the money,
don't worry.

155
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:53,633
Okay.

156
00:06:53,733 --> 00:06:54,800
[ELEVATOR DOORS SLIDE OPEN]

157
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:09,367
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

158
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:11,133
[MUSIC FADING OUT]

159
00:07:11,233 --> 00:07:12,667
[RAFAEL]
Email from the grave?

160
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,467
Why was it only sent now?

161
00:07:15,867 --> 00:07:18,400
I think Papa was
protecting something.

162
00:07:19,367 --> 00:07:21,300
He didn't want just anyone
to see it.

163
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,667
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

164
00:07:22,767 --> 00:07:23,733
See what?

165
00:07:34,333 --> 00:07:35,967
Five hundred fifty-six
million dollars?!

166
00:07:36,067 --> 00:07:37,000
Bro!

167
00:07:38,033 --> 00:07:39,200
- Sorry, bro.
- Shh!

168
00:07:40,033 --> 00:07:41,833
[WHISPERS] Five hundred
fifty-six million dollars?

169
00:07:43,433 --> 00:07:45,333
Seriously?
That's a lot of money, bro.

170
00:07:46,033 --> 00:07:49,000
It's a crypto wallet,
all in USTD.

171
00:07:50,467 --> 00:07:53,200
One USTD is equivalent
to one US dollar.

172
00:07:53,300 --> 00:07:56,333
So, that's over
32 billion pesos.

173
00:07:56,433 --> 00:07:59,033
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

174
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:01,867
You think this is the money
your father scammed?

175
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:03,867
Yes.

176
00:08:04,033 --> 00:08:07,700
That's why he converted it
to crypto to keep it hidden.

177
00:08:07,867 --> 00:08:10,267
You can't deposit that
much money in the bank

178
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:11,767
without getting flagged.

179
00:08:12,633 --> 00:08:14,833
In crypto, you can get away
with smooth transactions.

180
00:08:14,933 --> 00:08:18,567
Your only identity
is your wallet address.

181
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:22,400
If you're careful enough,
it can't be traced to you.

182
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:26,200
Even the government
can't freeze the funds, bro.

183
00:08:26,300 --> 00:08:29,233
Because only you have control
over the crypto wallet.

184
00:08:29,933 --> 00:08:32,900
But did your father really
scam this much money?

185
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:34,567
[SAMUEL] I don't know.
[INHALES DEEPLY]

186
00:08:34,733 --> 00:08:36,633
It sounds impossible.

187
00:08:36,767 --> 00:08:38,433
This is way too much money.

188
00:08:39,467 --> 00:08:42,233
He might have
other illegal schemes.

189
00:08:42,333 --> 00:08:48,267
[MUSIC BECOMES TENSE]

190
00:08:48,433 --> 00:08:50,900
Bro, if I can access
this crypto wallet,

191
00:08:51,067 --> 00:08:53,733
I can return the scammed
money to the victims

192
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:56,533
and all my problems
will finally be over.

193
00:08:57,300 --> 00:08:58,967
Here it is.

194
00:08:59,133 --> 00:09:00,433
What are you waiting for?

195
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:01,800
It's not that easy.

196
00:09:02,633 --> 00:09:04,733
With a blockchain explorer,

197
00:09:04,833 --> 00:09:06,667
I can check
what's in a crypto wallet,

198
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:08,633
but I can't transfer the money.

199
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:11,267
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

200
00:09:11,367 --> 00:09:15,767
To access this crypto wallet,
I need the seed phrase.

201
00:09:16,667 --> 00:09:18,633
W-What's that?

202
00:09:20,333 --> 00:09:21,900
When you create a crypto wallet,

203
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:25,100
it simultaneously generates
its seed phrase.

204
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:28,967
It usually contains
12 to 24 random words,

205
00:09:29,167 --> 00:09:32,033
depending on your
desired level of security.

206
00:09:32,167 --> 00:09:36,467
This combination is the only key
to access the wallet.

207
00:09:36,633 --> 00:09:39,467
In layman's terms,

208
00:09:39,633 --> 00:09:42,033
it's the equivalent
of a password.

209
00:09:42,167 --> 00:09:43,467
That's why even if someone

210
00:09:43,633 --> 00:09:45,133
knows all the words
in the seed phrase,

211
00:09:45,300 --> 00:09:47,767
they still need to enter them
in the correct order.

212
00:09:47,867 --> 00:09:52,300
I thought the word "ivory"
was my first word,

213
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,100
so I confirmed it
with my mother.

214
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,833
Turns out it's not, bro.

215
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:59,600
Ivory is the first word
of the seed phrase.

216
00:10:01,533 --> 00:10:02,667
What are the other words?

217
00:10:02,833 --> 00:10:05,633
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

218
00:10:05,733 --> 00:10:06,967
I don't know.

219
00:10:08,867 --> 00:10:10,700
Your father is so strange.

220
00:10:11,767 --> 00:10:13,200
He really is.

221
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:17,667
Would I be in this situation
if he wasn't like that?

222
00:10:18,767 --> 00:10:21,667
Maybe he didn't put
all the words in the email

223
00:10:21,767 --> 00:10:24,000
so other people
wouldn't intercept it.

224
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:25,133
He has faith in you

225
00:10:25,233 --> 00:10:28,167
because he knows you'll
figure out what these are.

226
00:10:28,267 --> 00:10:35,067
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

227
00:10:43,733 --> 00:10:45,267
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

228
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:47,400
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

229
00:10:47,567 --> 00:10:48,767
Seed phrase.

230
00:10:49,467 --> 00:10:51,333
Seed phrase.
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

231
00:10:51,433 --> 00:10:53,200
I need to find the seed phrase.

232
00:10:57,233 --> 00:10:59,200
Pa! Pa!

233
00:10:59,933 --> 00:11:07,000
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

234
00:11:14,933 --> 00:11:16,633
[SAMUEL] Seed phrase...

235
00:11:17,767 --> 00:11:19,233
[MUMBLING] Seed phrase...

236
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:22,233
What's the seed phrase?

237
00:11:22,333 --> 00:11:23,633
Seed phrase...

238
00:11:23,767 --> 00:11:28,067
- [OBJECTS CLATTERING]
- [PAPER RUSTLING]

239
00:11:28,167 --> 00:11:32,433
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

240
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:33,700
[OBJECT THUDS]

241
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:40,767
- [PAPER RUSTLING]
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

242
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:49,100
[SAMUEL] Where can I find it?

243
00:11:49,267 --> 00:11:55,267
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]
- [OBJECTS CLATTERING]

244
00:11:55,367 --> 00:12:02,167
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

245
00:12:08,433 --> 00:12:10,233
[SAMUEL] The laptop
was just placed there, but...

246
00:12:10,333 --> 00:12:11,433
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

247
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:12,767
where is it now?

248
00:12:12,867 --> 00:12:19,933
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

249
00:12:25,233 --> 00:12:26,667
[LOLITA] Samuel.

250
00:12:26,800 --> 00:12:27,600
Ma.

251
00:12:27,733 --> 00:12:29,433
Your son doesn't want
to go to school.

252
00:12:31,467 --> 00:12:34,000
- Why?
- He's being bullied.

253
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:37,700
Kids are saying his dad
and grandpa are scammers.

254
00:12:37,833 --> 00:12:44,667
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

255
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:47,700
[KING SOBS]

256
00:12:51,267 --> 00:12:52,400
Son?

257
00:12:53,167 --> 00:12:56,667
Dad, don't make me
go to school, please.

258
00:13:00,333 --> 00:13:01,400
But...

259
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:05,467
You can't just skip school.

260
00:13:06,567 --> 00:13:08,067
Son, those bullies...

261
00:13:09,533 --> 00:13:11,567
they're all just talk.

262
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,733
You have to be tough.

263
00:13:14,867 --> 00:13:16,467
Just ignore them.

264
00:13:17,733 --> 00:13:21,867
[SNIFFLES] I have classmates
whose parents were scammed.

265
00:13:23,033 --> 00:13:24,933
They hate me.

266
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:27,433
Some of them bully me.

267
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:30,733
Daddy will fix this, okay?

268
00:13:32,067 --> 00:13:34,100
Alright? Daddy will fix this.

269
00:13:34,233 --> 00:13:35,767
This will be over soon.

270
00:13:36,567 --> 00:13:38,233
[SNIFFLES, SOBS SOFTLY]

271
00:13:38,367 --> 00:13:41,200
They're calling you
a scammer, Daddy.

272
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:46,433
The police are
going to arrest you.

273
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:49,600
I'm going to lose you.

274
00:13:49,767 --> 00:13:50,667
No.

275
00:13:52,600 --> 00:13:57,100
No, I told you,
Daddy's not going anywhere.

276
00:13:59,233 --> 00:14:00,900
I am not going anywhere.

277
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,467
[WHIMPERS]

278
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:11,933
[SNIFFLES, CRIES]

279
00:14:13,333 --> 00:14:19,133
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

280
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:20,433
[TEACHER] Mr. Trinidad,

281
00:14:20,567 --> 00:14:22,867
we have a zero-tolerance
policy on bullying

282
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:23,967
in our school.

283
00:14:24,100 --> 00:14:24,967
With that said,

284
00:14:25,133 --> 00:14:25,967
Mr. Trinidad,

285
00:14:26,133 --> 00:14:30,967
we cannot control
the kids' emotions.

286
00:14:31,133 --> 00:14:33,500
So, what are you saying?

287
00:14:33,667 --> 00:14:35,500
There's nothing you can do?

288
00:14:35,633 --> 00:14:37,267
[TEACHER]
 We can conduct seminars

289
00:14:37,367 --> 00:14:38,567
to remind the kids

290
00:14:38,700 --> 00:14:39,967
that what they're doing
is wrong.

291
00:14:40,100 --> 00:14:43,233
But a lot of our
students' parents are mad

292
00:14:43,367 --> 00:14:45,467
and blame you
and your father.

293
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:48,833
Ma'am, I had nothing
to do with that.

294
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,967
[TEACHER] Yes,
 you already said that.

295
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:52,433
But right now,

296
00:14:52,533 --> 00:14:54,567
while things are still tense,

297
00:14:54,700 --> 00:14:57,567
I suggest homeschooling King.

298
00:14:57,700 --> 00:14:59,500
For your peace of mind.

299
00:14:59,667 --> 00:15:01,067
And for your information,

300
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:04,300
even our teachers
fell victim to this scam.

301
00:15:04,467 --> 00:15:05,633
Even me.

302
00:15:05,733 --> 00:15:08,433
I can control the teachers,

303
00:15:08,567 --> 00:15:11,033
but the parents and
what they tell their kids,

304
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:12,333
that's out of my hands.

305
00:15:12,467 --> 00:15:14,367
Think about it, Mr. Trinidad.

306
00:15:14,533 --> 00:15:15,500
Thank you.

307
00:15:15,633 --> 00:15:18,867
- [LINE DROPS]
- Ma'am. Ma'am!

308
00:15:19,033 --> 00:15:20,533
[PHONE RINGS]

309
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:23,867
What's up, bro?

310
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,133
Bad news again?

311
00:15:25,867 --> 00:15:28,100
[RAFAEL] Bro,
I sent you a video link.

312
00:15:28,233 --> 00:15:29,167
Watch it.

313
00:15:29,300 --> 00:15:32,367
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

314
00:15:32,500 --> 00:15:33,800
[PODCASTER]
 Samuel Trinidad,

315
00:15:33,900 --> 00:15:36,033
who is the manager of
the Golden Trust Bank,

316
00:15:36,233 --> 00:15:38,033
is Mike Trinidad's son.

317
00:15:38,167 --> 00:15:43,067
Last week, Mike Trinidad
was at that bank.

318
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:48,367
So, I think that's where
he's hiding our money.

319
00:15:48,500 --> 00:15:51,000
That bank will pay.

320
00:15:51,767 --> 00:15:53,067
They're an accomplice
to the crime.

321
00:15:54,167 --> 00:15:55,567
You'll all rot in jail!

322
00:15:55,733 --> 00:15:58,833
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

323
00:15:58,933 --> 00:15:59,867
[HUFFS]

324
00:16:01,433 --> 00:16:02,567
[SHOUTS]

325
00:16:15,033 --> 00:16:16,167
Mr. Gomez.

326
00:16:16,300 --> 00:16:17,200
Mm!

327
00:16:18,067 --> 00:16:19,367
General Ramirez.

328
00:16:19,467 --> 00:16:20,933
- How are you?
- I'm good.

329
00:16:21,067 --> 00:16:23,233
- Would you like to join me?
- No, I'm fine.

330
00:16:23,367 --> 00:16:24,700
Go ahead.

331
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:25,900
Continue with
what you're doing.

332
00:16:26,033 --> 00:16:28,733
I just dropped by
to say hi, and...

333
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:32,000
I won't take up
your time anymore.

334
00:16:32,133 --> 00:16:35,100
I know you're busy trying
to save the Golden Trust Bank.

335
00:16:35,267 --> 00:16:37,400
I admit, we took a hit,

336
00:16:37,533 --> 00:16:40,233
but, it's manageable, General.

337
00:16:40,367 --> 00:16:41,400
Really?

338
00:16:41,567 --> 00:16:42,633
Well, that's good to hear.

339
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:47,633
I heard about the news

340
00:16:48,567 --> 00:16:51,467
that Mike Trinidad's
involved in a scandal,

341
00:16:51,633 --> 00:16:55,100
and his son happens to be

342
00:16:55,967 --> 00:16:59,300
your bank manager,
unfortunately.

343
00:16:59,467 --> 00:17:02,133
[FINGER SNAPS]
What's his son's name?

344
00:17:02,267 --> 00:17:04,200
Samuel Trinidad.

345
00:17:05,300 --> 00:17:07,433
Samuel Trinidad,
Samuel Trinidad.

346
00:17:07,567 --> 00:17:09,300
Yeah, yeah. That's the guy.

347
00:17:10,667 --> 00:17:13,800
Adam, in the
world of banking,

348
00:17:14,767 --> 00:17:16,167
optics is everything,
right?

349
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:22,333
Business runs on the trust
of the depositors,

350
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:28,233
as well as their opinion
of you.

351
00:17:29,933 --> 00:17:33,100
If they find out that you are
associated with a scammer,

352
00:17:34,433 --> 00:17:36,300
naturally, they'll be worried.

353
00:17:36,433 --> 00:17:37,733
And the next move is,

354
00:17:38,700 --> 00:17:40,833
they may take
their business elsewhere.

355
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,667
But anyway, I'm not worried.

356
00:17:44,833 --> 00:17:47,333
You said your bank took a hit,

357
00:17:47,467 --> 00:17:49,000
but it's manageable.

358
00:17:49,167 --> 00:17:50,600
I trust you.

359
00:17:50,733 --> 00:17:53,600
I know you can save this bank

360
00:17:53,733 --> 00:17:58,100
that you spent your
entire life building.

361
00:17:58,700 --> 00:17:59,633
Good job.

362
00:17:59,733 --> 00:18:01,433
Thank you, General.

363
00:18:01,567 --> 00:18:02,800
Yeah. Go back to your meal.

364
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:04,333
- Thank you.
- See you around.

365
00:18:04,467 --> 00:18:11,333
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

366
00:18:16,833 --> 00:18:19,867
[PHONE RINGING]

367
00:18:21,233 --> 00:18:24,033
[HELEN] I thought you were
 coming home after the burial?

368
00:18:24,733 --> 00:18:25,733
I went to Boracay.

369
00:18:25,900 --> 00:18:27,400
I needed a break.

370
00:18:27,533 --> 00:18:29,200
A break from what?

371
00:18:29,333 --> 00:18:31,833
All you do is party,

372
00:18:31,933 --> 00:18:34,000
which you'll probably do
again now that you're back.

373
00:18:34,733 --> 00:18:36,567
Ma, what's the problem?

374
00:18:36,700 --> 00:18:38,467
I don't even live with you
anymore.

375
00:18:38,600 --> 00:18:40,400
Why are you waiting for me
to get home?

376
00:18:40,567 --> 00:18:42,233
[SIGHS] Well...

377
00:18:43,033 --> 00:18:46,633
I've been reading
posts about your dad.

378
00:18:46,767 --> 00:18:50,967
Ari, even his son
was involved in the scam.

379
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:52,700
Everyone's mad at them.

380
00:18:52,833 --> 00:18:54,533
What if you get involved?

381
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:57,400
I'm on my way
to airport to go home.

382
00:18:57,533 --> 00:18:59,267
Besides, nobody here knows me.

383
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:00,767
So, chill, okay?

384
00:19:00,900 --> 00:19:02,767
[HELEN'S HUSBAND] Helen,
 have you seen my purple shirt?

385
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:05,033
- Helen?
- Coming.

386
00:19:05,133 --> 00:19:07,833
Oh, your husband
is looking for you.

387
00:19:07,967 --> 00:19:10,200
Is that Ari
bothering you again?

388
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:12,233
Hey, Ari.

389
00:19:12,367 --> 00:19:14,067
Why don't you stay
in the Philippines

390
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:16,067
and stop calling us?
Okay?

391
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:17,100
"Us?"

392
00:19:17,267 --> 00:19:18,500
Did I call you?

393
00:19:18,633 --> 00:19:20,267
I didn't, right?

394
00:19:20,433 --> 00:19:21,600
What?

395
00:19:21,767 --> 00:19:23,100
What did you say?

396
00:19:23,267 --> 00:19:24,600
You married a Filipina

397
00:19:24,733 --> 00:19:26,733
yet didn't bother
to learn Tagalog?

398
00:19:26,867 --> 00:19:28,767
What a prick.

399
00:19:28,933 --> 00:19:30,700
Babe, what'd she say?

400
00:19:30,833 --> 00:19:32,233
Hey, George.

401
00:19:32,333 --> 00:19:33,300
What?

402
00:19:33,433 --> 00:19:34,567
Suck it, loser.

403
00:19:34,667 --> 00:19:35,600
What?

404
00:19:35,733 --> 00:19:36,800
What did she say?

405
00:19:41,767 --> 00:19:48,800
[CROWD CLAMORING]

406
00:19:58,833 --> 00:20:01,800
Scammers don't
need protection.

407
00:20:02,700 --> 00:20:05,467
They should fend
for themselves.

408
00:20:05,600 --> 00:20:07,333
[CLAMORING CONTINUES]

409
00:20:07,467 --> 00:20:10,000
[JOHNNY] Sir, good morning.

410
00:20:11,033 --> 00:20:14,167
You should go in,
before it gets messy out here.

411
00:20:16,933 --> 00:20:20,300
[CLAMOR, SHOUTS]

412
00:20:30,267 --> 00:20:31,767
Sir, sir.

413
00:20:32,467 --> 00:20:33,433
What?

414
00:20:33,533 --> 00:20:36,067
You need to see
our transactions.

415
00:20:36,233 --> 00:20:37,367
What?

416
00:20:37,533 --> 00:20:38,500
Why?

417
00:20:38,633 --> 00:20:39,800
What happened?

418
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:46,767
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

419
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:48,467
"Current Balance"

420
00:20:50,067 --> 00:20:51,767
[EMPLOYEE] Sir,
our deposit balance

421
00:20:51,900 --> 00:20:53,500
was 25 billion yesterday.

422
00:20:53,633 --> 00:20:54,667
That's what's left.

423
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:56,200
And it keeps going down.

424
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:58,033
Who authorized this?

425
00:20:58,200 --> 00:21:00,467
I didn't approve
these withdrawals.

426
00:21:01,567 --> 00:21:02,467
Sir.

427
00:21:04,533 --> 00:21:05,433
"001"

428
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:10,167
This is the head office.
It was the president.

429
00:21:12,767 --> 00:21:14,667
He's shutting down
this branch.

430
00:21:14,767 --> 00:21:16,033
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

431
00:21:17,900 --> 00:21:24,733
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

432
00:21:27,667 --> 00:21:30,333
[GUARD] Sir, you can't park
your car there.

433
00:21:36,900 --> 00:21:43,800
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

434
00:21:50,533 --> 00:21:52,100
[ASSISTANT] Sir, you can't
go in there.

435
00:21:52,233 --> 00:21:53,567
[SAMUEL] President Gomez.

436
00:21:54,533 --> 00:21:57,367
- [ASSISTANT] Guard! Guard!
- This is a board meeting.

437
00:21:57,533 --> 00:21:59,400
What the hell are you
doing here?!

438
00:22:07,567 --> 00:22:08,933
- [IMMIGRATION OFFICER] Enjoy.
- Thank you.

439
00:22:09,067 --> 00:22:12,067
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

440
00:22:12,233 --> 00:22:13,433
[IMMIGRATION OFFICER]
Thank you.

441
00:22:20,667 --> 00:22:21,567
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

442
00:22:27,267 --> 00:22:29,100
Ms. Arissa Trinidad,

443
00:22:29,267 --> 00:22:32,233
can you please confirm
your father's full name?

444
00:22:32,333 --> 00:22:34,100
Miguel Trinidad. Why?

445
00:22:34,267 --> 00:22:37,233
Also known as Mike Trinidad?

446
00:22:37,333 --> 00:22:39,267
Yes. W-What's this about?

447
00:22:39,433 --> 00:22:41,467
Ms. Trinidad, I'm sorry,

448
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:44,133
but can you please
step aside for a moment?

449
00:22:44,267 --> 00:22:46,133
Why? What's the problem?

450
00:22:46,267 --> 00:22:48,300
I'm afraid your name
has been flagged.

451
00:22:48,467 --> 00:22:51,600
Flagged?
What does that mean?

452
00:22:51,767 --> 00:22:53,933
Well, it means that
your name has been

453
00:22:54,100 --> 00:22:55,767
on the DOJ's watch list order,

454
00:22:55,867 --> 00:22:59,133
and we have to sort it out
before you can board.

455
00:22:59,300 --> 00:23:01,233
M-My plane leaves in an hour.

456
00:23:01,333 --> 00:23:03,767
I'm sorry. Bro.

457
00:23:03,933 --> 00:23:05,567
Please follow this gentleman
to the secondary screening.

458
00:23:05,667 --> 00:23:07,933
This is ridiculous.
I haven't done anything wrong.

459
00:23:08,100 --> 00:23:09,833
Ms. Trinidad,
if this is a mistake,

460
00:23:09,967 --> 00:23:11,000
we'll sort this out.

461
00:23:11,133 --> 00:23:13,933
But as of the moment,
you cannot leave the country.

462
00:23:14,967 --> 00:23:16,600
- [SCOFFS]
- [IMMIGRATION OFFICER] Please.

463
00:23:16,767 --> 00:23:23,600
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

464
00:23:27,167 --> 00:23:29,500
She's Mike Trinidad's daughter?

465
00:23:29,667 --> 00:23:30,767
[IMMIGRATION OFFICER] Next.

466
00:23:32,467 --> 00:23:37,967
Sir, you authorized large-amount
withdrawals from my branch.

467
00:23:38,133 --> 00:23:39,967
Yes, I did.

468
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:44,533
Our clients are coming
directly to me.

469
00:23:44,667 --> 00:23:47,133
- Do you know why, Samuel?
- Sir.

470
00:23:47,233 --> 00:23:48,867
They don't want to talk
to you anymore.

471
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:50,467
Sir...

472
00:23:50,567 --> 00:23:52,500
All of those withdrawals,

473
00:23:52,667 --> 00:23:55,467
they are not just withdrawing
from your bank,

474
00:23:55,667 --> 00:24:00,300
they are withdrawing their money
from Golden Trust Bank

475
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:02,867
and putting it
in other banks!

476
00:24:03,033 --> 00:24:05,000
And it's all because of you.

477
00:24:05,167 --> 00:24:08,700
You got my bank into this mess.

478
00:24:08,867 --> 00:24:10,167
Sir, please believe me,

479
00:24:10,267 --> 00:24:13,000
I had nothing to do
with my father's dealings.

480
00:24:13,167 --> 00:24:14,333
I had nothing to do with it.

481
00:24:14,500 --> 00:24:16,667
I don't care about that anymore.

482
00:24:16,833 --> 00:24:19,400
Do you know why we called
this board meeting?

483
00:24:19,533 --> 00:24:21,700
Because of what's
happening now.

484
00:24:22,833 --> 00:24:26,400
Anyway, [CHUCKLES]
it's good that you're here.

485
00:24:26,533 --> 00:24:29,467
Because you're one of the
agendas of this board meeting.

486
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:45,700
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

487
00:24:45,867 --> 00:24:48,033
Effective immediately,

488
00:24:48,967 --> 00:24:52,700
you are terminated
from Golden Trust Bank.

489
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:04,900
[ELLEN] I knew it.

490
00:25:05,067 --> 00:25:07,700
If you had gone straight home,

491
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:10,967
you wouldn't have gotten
dragged into that issue.

492
00:25:11,833 --> 00:25:13,233
Ma, I don't need this
right now.

493
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:15,400
Can you please stop
nagging me?

494
00:25:15,500 --> 00:25:18,400
Don't act so arrogant
when you're the one at fault.

495
00:25:18,567 --> 00:25:20,367
What are you going to do now?

496
00:25:21,767 --> 00:25:23,100
I don't know.

497
00:25:23,267 --> 00:25:25,267
Just let me think.

498
00:25:25,433 --> 00:25:28,233
Oh, really? When have you
ever used your head?

499
00:25:28,333 --> 00:25:29,533
Ma!

500
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:38,067
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

501
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:39,333
Sir, this is unfair.

502
00:25:39,467 --> 00:25:41,767
Unfair?
You know what's unfair?

503
00:25:42,767 --> 00:25:46,167
That they are losing confidence
in Golden Trust Bank

504
00:25:46,300 --> 00:25:48,000
because of you
and your father!

505
00:25:48,133 --> 00:25:50,767
I'm innocent. I'm innocent.

506
00:25:50,933 --> 00:25:54,933
It doesn't matter.
You know, you are now poison.

507
00:25:55,033 --> 00:25:57,167
If you stay in this bank,

508
00:25:57,300 --> 00:26:00,933
people will lose confidence
and trust in us!

509
00:26:01,033 --> 00:26:05,100
A bank run may even start
because you are still here!

510
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:09,000
I have been loyal
to this company.

511
00:26:09,167 --> 00:26:10,633
I have been loyal, sir!

512
00:26:10,733 --> 00:26:13,833
Loyalty means nothing to me.

513
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:15,533
No, no, no, no, no, no.

514
00:26:15,667 --> 00:26:18,833
This is illegal termination.
I'm taking this to court.

515
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:20,633
I'm taking this to court.

516
00:26:20,800 --> 00:26:22,700
[MR. GOMEZ] Go ahead, Samuel.

517
00:26:22,833 --> 00:26:25,633
I am willing to lose
a few million pesos

518
00:26:25,733 --> 00:26:29,833
on labor cases instead of losing
billions from my bank!

519
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:34,633
I'm going to make sure
that you go bankrupt

520
00:26:34,733 --> 00:26:37,833
from attorney fees
and legal fees.

521
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:41,300
And I am going to love
every minute of it.

522
00:26:41,467 --> 00:26:42,833
Get him out of here!

523
00:26:43,033 --> 00:26:44,500
- Sir, let's talk about this.
- Come with us.

524
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:45,667
- Wait!
- Get him out!

525
00:26:45,833 --> 00:26:47,200
I never want to see you again!

526
00:26:47,367 --> 00:26:49,900
Mr. Gomez, let's talk about
this. I can leave on my own.

527
00:26:50,033 --> 00:26:51,333
Wait! Sir!

528
00:26:51,500 --> 00:26:58,500
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

529
00:27:06,033 --> 00:27:07,833
Good day, Ms. Trinidad.
Welcome back.

530
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:10,167
I thought your flight
was this morning.

531
00:27:10,333 --> 00:27:11,800
Long story.
I just want to rest.

532
00:27:11,900 --> 00:27:14,300
And please give me my old room.
I liked the view.

533
00:27:14,400 --> 00:27:16,067
It'll cheer me up.

534
00:27:16,233 --> 00:27:17,567
Sure, Ms. Trinidad.

535
00:27:20,533 --> 00:27:21,667
[DEVICE BEEPS]

536
00:27:27,267 --> 00:27:28,400
[DEVICE BEEPS]

537
00:27:35,367 --> 00:27:39,333
Um, Ms. Trinidad,
do you have other cards?

538
00:27:39,433 --> 00:27:40,900
This card was declined.

539
00:27:41,067 --> 00:27:45,533
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

540
00:27:45,700 --> 00:27:47,533
Let go of me. Let go!

541
00:27:48,600 --> 00:27:49,900
I can walk from here.

542
00:27:52,433 --> 00:27:53,600
Hey, watch it!

543
00:27:55,567 --> 00:27:58,800
Next time, watch where
you're going.

544
00:27:59,667 --> 00:28:01,100
You bumped into me.

545
00:28:02,467 --> 00:28:03,800
What's with the temper?

546
00:28:05,100 --> 00:28:08,133
You're the one who's not
looking where you're going.

547
00:28:11,133 --> 00:28:12,467
Is there a problem?

548
00:28:14,600 --> 00:28:16,900
You look like someone
who just got fired.

549
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:18,133
What did you say?

550
00:28:25,133 --> 00:28:26,167
I know you.

551
00:28:27,700 --> 00:28:28,933
You're the...

552
00:28:30,167 --> 00:28:31,267
...scammer.

553
00:28:31,367 --> 00:28:38,267
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

554
00:28:47,433 --> 00:28:49,100
All my life,

555
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:51,633
I've always wanted
to get away from Papa.

556
00:28:52,800 --> 00:28:54,767
I want to live my own life.

557
00:28:55,667 --> 00:28:58,533
I want to feel like
I'm not like my father.

558
00:28:58,667 --> 00:29:00,267
But in the end,

559
00:29:00,367 --> 00:29:02,600
people think
we're just the same.

560
00:29:02,700 --> 00:29:03,633
Scammers!

561
00:29:03,733 --> 00:29:06,467
[SULLEN MUSIC PLAYING]

562
00:29:06,567 --> 00:29:08,000
- [CHAIR THUDS]
- [INHALES SHARPLY]

563
00:29:08,167 --> 00:29:11,100
I can no longer claim
my severance pay, Ma.

564
00:29:13,167 --> 00:29:15,200
I've been terminated.

565
00:29:15,333 --> 00:29:19,000
Everything I worked hard for
is gone in an instant!

566
00:29:20,300 --> 00:29:21,467
- It's all gone!
- [TABLE SLAMS]

567
00:29:24,633 --> 00:29:26,467
All those might be gone.

568
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:29,000
But...

569
00:29:31,167 --> 00:29:34,533
- Dear, didn't we...
- [SAMUEL BREATHES SHARPLY]

570
00:29:34,700 --> 00:29:35,833
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

571
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:39,533
...come from nothing, dear?

572
00:29:43,867 --> 00:29:45,133
Dear...

573
00:29:46,700 --> 00:29:48,800
When your father left us,

574
00:29:49,900 --> 00:29:52,133
we struggled so much.

575
00:29:52,233 --> 00:29:53,567
We really did.

576
00:29:53,700 --> 00:29:56,200
I didn't even know how
I'd afford your schooling.

577
00:29:56,367 --> 00:29:58,233
[BREATHES SHARPLY, SNIFFLES]

578
00:30:00,200 --> 00:30:03,800
But you found a way
on your own, Samuel.

579
00:30:03,933 --> 00:30:05,867
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

580
00:30:05,967 --> 00:30:08,867
You were able
to secure a scholarship.

581
00:30:09,033 --> 00:30:10,867
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

582
00:30:11,033 --> 00:30:13,867
You even juggled a job
while studying.

583
00:30:14,033 --> 00:30:17,400
Dear, you've achieved a lot.

584
00:30:17,567 --> 00:30:18,867
Dear...

585
00:30:18,967 --> 00:30:21,833
Dear, you built
a good life for us.

586
00:30:21,933 --> 00:30:24,267
Look at all this.

587
00:30:24,400 --> 00:30:26,867
We live in this nice house...

588
00:30:26,967 --> 00:30:28,700
because of you, dear.

589
00:30:29,300 --> 00:30:32,900
[SOBBING, SNIFFLING]

590
00:30:33,067 --> 00:30:34,033
Ma...

591
00:30:34,133 --> 00:30:35,267
[SNIFFLES]

592
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:37,367
That was before, Ma.
[SNIFFLES]

593
00:30:37,500 --> 00:30:40,700
That's when people
didn't see me as a scammer.

594
00:30:40,800 --> 00:30:42,700
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

595
00:30:42,800 --> 00:30:44,400
[INHALES DEEPLY]

596
00:30:44,500 --> 00:30:45,533
Dear...

597
00:30:45,967 --> 00:30:48,033
Just like before...

598
00:30:48,133 --> 00:30:51,533
I know you can get
back on your feet.

599
00:30:52,767 --> 00:30:55,467
Because you're such
a strong person, dear.

600
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:58,800
You won't let yourself
fall without fighting!

601
00:31:01,100 --> 00:31:02,400
You're so strong!

602
00:31:03,400 --> 00:31:05,367
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

603
00:31:06,167 --> 00:31:07,400
Everything...

604
00:31:10,100 --> 00:31:11,833
Everything I've achieved
in my life...

605
00:31:11,967 --> 00:31:14,300
[SNIFFLING]

606
00:31:15,333 --> 00:31:17,633
...wouldn't be possible
without you.

607
00:31:17,800 --> 00:31:18,900
Samuel...

608
00:31:20,300 --> 00:31:22,433
When your dad and I separated,

609
00:31:24,700 --> 00:31:27,600
there was one thing
I made sure to do.

610
00:31:29,333 --> 00:31:32,133
That was for you to feel like
you have a loving family.

611
00:31:33,467 --> 00:31:36,567
And just like
what we did before...

612
00:31:37,867 --> 00:31:39,767
we will rise again.

613
00:31:39,933 --> 00:31:41,600
Dear, in this situation,

614
00:31:41,767 --> 00:31:45,767
you can make it
as a part of our family.

615
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:53,533
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

616
00:31:53,667 --> 00:31:54,533
Family?

617
00:31:56,967 --> 00:31:58,200
Family...

618
00:31:58,333 --> 00:32:01,833
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

619
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:03,967
- [BAG UNZIPS]
- Samuel?

620
00:32:04,067 --> 00:32:05,000
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

621
00:32:05,167 --> 00:32:07,000
[LAPTOP CLATTERING]

622
00:32:07,167 --> 00:32:08,000
Samuel, what's wrong?

623
00:32:08,167 --> 00:32:10,633
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

624
00:32:10,800 --> 00:32:12,667
Samuel, what's going on?

625
00:32:12,833 --> 00:32:14,500
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

626
00:32:15,500 --> 00:32:22,500
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

627
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:36,133
The government
will freeze

628
00:32:36,267 --> 00:32:38,500
all the accounts
under your dad's name.

629
00:32:38,667 --> 00:32:39,700
I'm trapped here.

630
00:32:40,533 --> 00:32:43,333
Those scammers
make me so angry.

631
00:32:43,433 --> 00:32:45,233
They are all heartless.

632
00:32:45,367 --> 00:32:46,467
You have no freedom

633
00:32:46,567 --> 00:32:49,333
if people see your family
as scammers.

634
00:32:49,467 --> 00:32:50,767
I need to find
the seed phrase.

635
00:32:50,900 --> 00:32:52,533
It's hidden
in a secret compartment.

636
00:32:52,700 --> 00:32:53,933
We can't let them
get ahead of us.

637
00:32:54,067 --> 00:32:56,700
All that money came
from the scam victims.

638
00:32:56,800 --> 00:32:59,933
That's the kind of money
you'd kill people for!
